<paragraph id="A23B8905FF92FFB50CEAFC92FD4EFC0A" blockId="2.[151,1436,886,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="8294AE2BFF92FFB50CEAFC92FD4EFC0A" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<treatmentCitation id="2325AF14FF92FFB50CEAFC92FDC7FC28" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[151,624,886,910]" page="204" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" year="1911">
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB50CEAFC92FDC7FC28" authority="Kieffer, 1911: 204" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityPageNumber="204" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,624,886,910]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB50CEAFC92FE1BFC28" box="[151,428,886,910]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Clystopsenella longiventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF92FFB50DCEFC92FDC7FC28" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[435,624,886,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="200 - 233" refId="ref6793" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1911) Nouveaux Bethylides et Drynides exotiques du British Museum de Londres. Annales de la Societe Scientifique de Bruxelles, 35 (2), 200 - 233." type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer, 1911: 204</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<typeStatus id="7D3F37A7FF92FFB50E07FC92FD68FC28" box="[634,735,886,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Lectotype</typeStatus>
female, designated by 
<treatmentCitation id="2325AF14FF92FFB50FB6FC92FBC2FC28" author="Evans, H. E." box="[971,1141,886,910]" page="10" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" year="1963">
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF92FFB50FB6FC92FBC2FC28" author="Evans, H. E." box="[971,1141,886,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="7 - 16" refId="ref6412" refString="Evans, H. E. (1963) A new family of wasps. Psyche, 70 (1), 7 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 1963 / 92486." type="journal article" year="1963">Evans (1963:10)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
, 
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF92FFB508FDFC92FB75FC28" box="[1152,1218,886,910]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Amazonas, Parintins (‘Villa Nova’) (NHM, examined through photographs).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<caption id="F6FBD98DFF92FFB50CEAF871FBE1F874" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531423" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6531423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531423/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" startId="2.[151,250,1941,1965]" targetBox="[151,1435,959,1918]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF92FFB50CEAF871FBE1F874" blockId="2.[151,1437,1941,2002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB50CEAF871FEA4F808" bold="true" box="[151,275,1941,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB50D64F872FD9AF808" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[281,557,1942,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB50D64F872FD9AF808" box="[281,557,1942,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Clystopsenella longiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lectotype female. A) habitus, lateral view, scale bar: 2 mm; B) head, frontal view, scale bar: 0.5 mm; C) habitus, dorsal view, scale bar: 2 mm; D) specimen and labels (both surfaces).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF93FFB40CEAFF73FD33FDBF" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
The species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF93FFB40D9AFF73FD30FF17" author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[487,647,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" pagination="200 - 233" refId="ref6793" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1911) Nouveaux Bethylides et Drynides exotiques du British Museum de Londres. Annales de la Societe Scientifique de Bruxelles, 35 (2), 200 - 233." type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer (1911)</bibRefCitation>
based on 
<specimenCount id="B482428CFF93FFB40E8AFF73FC2BFF17" box="[759,924,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="3ABF9580FF93FFB40FD7FF73FC40FF17" box="[938,1015,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1941,1965]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,959,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-268@2.[151,1435,959,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Clystopsenella longiventris lectotype female.A) habitus, lateral view, scale bar: 2 mm; B) head, frontal view, scale bar: 0.5 mm; C) habitus, dorsal view, scale bar: 2 mm; D) specimen and labels (both surfaces)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="3ABF9580FF93FFB40850FF73FB8BFF17" box="[1069,1084,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1539,1563]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,558,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-202@3.[151,1435,558,1513]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Clystopsenella longiventris paralectotype female. A) habitus, lateral view, scale bar: 1 mm; B) head, frontal view, scale bar: 0.5 mm; C) habitus, dorsal view, scale bar: 2 mm; D) specimen and labels (both surfaces)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">2</figureCitation>
) which, judging by the features of the locality labels, were collected by Henry W. Bates. These specimens were obtained during his trip through the Amazon Forest, but the precise indication of the type localities was never mentioned by subsequent authors. ‘St. Paul’ refers to the municipality of 
<collectingRegion id="604047E7FF93FFB40E26FEE7FD78FEBB" box="[603,719,259,285]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
de Olivença, in the Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion id="604047E7FF93FFB408F0FEE7FAB1FEBB" box="[1165,1286,259,285]" country="Colombia" name="Amazonas" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, while ‘Villa Nova’ refers to Parintins in the same state (
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF93FFB40E09FEC3FC96FEE7" author="Papavero, N." box="[628,801,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" refId="ref7260" refString="Papavero, N. (1973) Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Vol. 2. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 446 pp." type="book" year="1973">Papavero 1973</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="7D3F37A7FF93FFB40F18FEC3FC7BFEE7" box="[869,972,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="7D3F37A7FF93FFB4087CFEC3FB2FFEE7" box="[1025,1176,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">paralectotype</typeStatus>
are the only specimens known from the Brazilian Amazon. Considering that Bates was an avid collector of beetles, including cerambycids (
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF93FFB40CE2FE8BFE82FE2F" author="O'Hara, J. E." box="[159,309,366,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" pagination="195 - 219" refId="ref7158" refString="O'Hara, J. E. (1995) Henry Walter Bates - his life and contributions to biology. Archives of Natural History, 22, 195 - 219. https: // doi. org / 10.3366 / anh. 1995.22.2.195" type="journal article" year="1995">O’Hara 1995</bibRefCitation>
), it is possible that he reared the 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF93FFB40EE7FE8BFC88FE2F" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[666,831,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF93FFB40EE7FE8BFC88FE2F" box="[666,831,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Clystopsenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
wasps from parasitized beetle larvae. Additionally, the specimens exhibit a pattern of coloration of their integument with lighter areas. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF93FFB408EFFE77FA9EFE08" author="Evans, H. E." box="[1170,1321,403,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" pagination="7 - 16" refId="ref6412" refString="Evans, H. E. (1963) A new family of wasps. Psyche, 70 (1), 7 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 1963 / 92486." type="journal article" year="1963">Evans (1963)</bibRefCitation>
attributed lighter coloration in scolebythids to fading with time in collections, this condition is more likely indicative that the specimens were killed before reaching full sclerotization. The same color pattern is exhibited by the 
<specimenCount id="B482428CFF93FFB4096EFE3FFA2BFE53" box="[1299,1436,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingRegion id="604047E7FF93FFB40CA8FE1BFEA1FDBF" box="[213,278,511,537]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Bahia</collectingRegion>
reared from a cerambycid larva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="F6FBD98DFF93FFB40CEAF9E7FB38F999" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531425" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6531425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" startId="3.[151,250,1539,1563]" targetBox="[151,1435,558,1513]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF93FFB40CEAF9E7FB38F999" blockId="3.[151,1436,1539,1599]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF93FFB40CEAF9E7FEA4F9BD" bold="true" box="[151,275,1539,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF93FFB40D67F9E7FD98F9BD" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[282,559,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF93FFB40D67F9E7FD98F9BD" box="[282,559,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Clystopsenella longiventris</emphasis>
